Jim Naughten (British, b.1969) is an internationally-exhibited artist, with his work held in several private and public collections, including the Imperial War Museum in London. His photographs are the subject of two monographs, 'Re-enactors' (Hotshoe Books, 2009) and 'Conflict and Costume' (Merrell, 2013).
